Key Match Events: Cameron Johnson scored 26 points and Cam Thomas added 24
Brooklyn Nets led 111-90 with 6:55 remaining before missing their next 12 field-goal attempts
Damian Lillard scored five straight points to cap a 20-0 run and cut the deficit to 111-110 with 37.4 seconds remaining
After Milwaukee star Giannis Antetokounmpo missed a layup with 6.1 seconds left, the Nets’ Ziaire Williams sank two foul shots to make it a three-point game
Lillard missed a 3-point attempt on the Bucks’ next possession
Milwaukee had one final chance with 0.6 seconds left, but Lillard’s 35-foot shot fell short
